SELENIUM GRID - QUICK REVISION NOTES
====================================

1. WHAT IS SELENIUM GRID?
-------------------------
- Selenium Grid is a Selenium Component.
- Used to execute test cases on:
  * Multiple Operating Systems (Windows, Linux, Mac)
  * Multiple Browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Edge, Safari)
  * Multiple Machines

Examples:
- Windows + Chrome
- Linux + Firefox
- Mac + Safari

==================================================

2. MAIN COMPONENTS
------------------

A) HUB
------
- Central machine.
- Receives test execution requests.
- Controls all connected Nodes.
- Distributes tests to Nodes.

B) NODE
-------
- Remote machine connected to Hub.
- Executes actual test cases.
- Can have one OS and multiple browsers.

Architecture:

            HUB
          /  |  \
         /   |   \
     Node1 Node2 Node3

==================================================

3. WHY SELENIUM GRID?
---------------------

Without Grid:
- Tests run only on local machine.

With Grid:
- Cross Browser Testing.
- Cross Platform Testing.
- Parallel Execution.
- Faster execution.

==================================================

4. GRID SETUP TYPES
-------------------

A) STANDALONE SETUP
-------------------
- Hub and Node are in the same machine.
- Mainly used for learning and small projects.

Local Machine
      |
 Hub + Node

B) DISTRIBUTED SETUP
--------------------
- One Hub Machine.
- Multiple Node Machines.

Hub Machine
      |
-------------------
|        |        |
Node1   Node2   Node3

==================================================

5. HOW NODES CAN BE CREATED?
----------------------------

1. Physical Machines
   - Separate Computers

2. Virtual Machines (VMs)
   - Windows VM
   - Linux VM
   - Mac VM

3. Docker Containers (Modern Approach)
   - Download Docker Image
   - Create Container
   - Container acts like a lightweight machine
   - Register Container as Selenium Node

Linux Image
      |
  Container
      |
 Selenium Node

==================================================

