8. INTERVIEW QUESTION
---------------------

Q) If TestNG can run tests in parallel,
   why do we need Selenium Grid?

Answer:

TestNG:
- Parallel execution framework.
- Runs tests simultaneously.
- Usually on same machine.
- Same OS environment.

Selenium Grid:
- Distributed execution infrastructure.
- Runs tests on different machines.
- Runs tests on different OS.
- Runs tests on different browsers.
- Supports Cross Browser Testing.

Example:

TestNG Parallel:
Chrome + Edge
on same Windows machine

Selenium Grid:
Chrome on Windows
Firefox on Linux
Safari on Mac

==================================================

9. IMPORTANT POINT
------------------

TestNG = Parallel Execution Framework

Selenium Grid = Distributed Execution Infrastructure

In real projects:
TestNG + Selenium Grid are often used together.

==================================================

10. ONE-LINE INTERVIEW DEFINITION
---------------------------------

"Selenium Grid is used to execute Selenium test cases
across multiple machines, operating systems, and
browsers simultaneously from a central Hub, enabling
parallel and cross-browser testing."

==================================================

11. KEY INTERVIEW POINTS
------------------------

Q) Can Selenium Grid work with a single machine?
A) Yes. This is called Standalone Grid Setup.

Q) Is Selenium Grid useful with a single node?
A) Technically yes, but major benefits come when
   multiple nodes/machines are connected.

Q) What is the main advantage of Selenium Grid?
A) Cross Browser + Cross Platform Testing.

Q) Can TestNG replace Selenium Grid?
A) No.

TestNG -> Parallel execution.
Selenium Grid -> Distributed execution.

Both solve different problems and are often used together.